     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="25"/>
   <head>The Authors Friend to
the Booke.</head>
   <l>
      <seg rend="decorInit">G</seg>Oe ventrous booke, thy selfe expose</l>
   <l>To learned men, and none but those;</l>
   <l>For this carping age of ours</l>
   <l>Snuffes at all but choycest flowers,</l>
   <l>Cul'd from out the curious knots</l>
   <l>Of quaint writers garden plots;</l>
   <l>These they smell at, these they savor,</l>
   <l>Yet not free from feare, nor favour:</l>
   <l>But if thou wert smel'd a right</l>
   <l>By a nose not stuft with spight,</l>
   <l>Thou to all that learning love</l>
   <l>Might'st a fragrant nosegay prove,</l>
   <l>So content thee, till due time,</l>
   <l>Blazethy worth throughout this Clime.</l>
</div>
